<29-1,Mary Alice Voiceover>But...
<29-1,Mary Alice Voiceover>但是...

642
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:39,300
<28-10,Edie>there is something I want you to do for me.
<28-10,Edie>我想要你为我做些事

643
00:39:39,300 --> 00:39:41,100
<28-11,Susan>Of course. Anything.
<28-11,Susan>当然. 任何事都可以

644
00:39:41,100 --> 00:39:43,100
<28-11,Susan>You name it. What?
<28-11,Susan>你说吧. 什么事?

645
00:39:43,100 --> 00:39:45,900
<28-12,Edie>I want to be invited to your poker game.
<28-12,Edie>我想要被邀请参加你们的扑克游戏

646
00:39:45,900 --> 00:39:46,900
<29-5,Mary Alice Voiceover>Our poker games?
<29-5,Mary Alice Voiceover>我们的扑克游戏?

647
00:39:46,900 --> 00:39:51,500
<28-14,Edie>I'm not saying I'll go, and I'm not saying that you and your little friends have to be nice to me,
<28-14,Edie>我没说我要参加, 我也没说 你和你的那些小伙伴要对我好一点

648
00:39:51,500 --> 00:39:57,400
<28-14,Edie>but every once in a while, yeah, it'd be nice to be asked.
<28-14,Edie>不过时不时地, 嗯, 被邀请也很愉快

649
00:39:58,500 --> 00:40:04,200
<28-15,Susan>Well, uh, we meet on tuesdays, and it's potluck lunch. Everybody has to bring something.
<28-15,Susan>嗯, 我们周二见面, 中饭是家常便饭 每个人都要带些东西

650
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:05,300
<28-16,Edie>I'm not bringing anything.
<28-16,Edie>我不会带任何东西

651
00:40:05,300 --> 00:40:07,900
<28-17,Susan>Oh, you don't have to.
<28-17,Susan>哦, 你不必带

652
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:11,400
<28-17,Susan>Well, this is good.
<28-17,Susan>那很好

653
00:40:11,700 --> 00:40:13,900
<28-17,Susan>Thank you.
<28-17,Susan>谢谢

654
00:40:15,200 --> 00:40:18,300
<28-17,Susan>I guess I should go take a shower and...
<28-17,Susan>我想我该去洗个淋浴...

655
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:21,900
<28-17,Susan>wash Mrs. Huber off me.
<28-17,Susan>把Huber夫人从身上洗掉

656
00:40:22,300 --> 00:40:23,700
<29-2,Mary Alice Voiceover>Hold it.
<29-2,Mary Alice Voiceover>等一下

657
00:40:23,700 --> 00:40:30,900
<28-18,Edie>I can't stand the thought of Martha's ashes going down some sewer drain.
<28-18,Edie>想到Huber夫人将被冲到下水道去 真是让我难以忍受

658
00:40:30,900 --> 00:40:34,500
<28-19,Susan>Well, Edie, I-I have to clean up.
<28-19,Susan>Edie, 我必须清洗一下

659
00:40:34,500 --> 00:40:38,200
<28-20,Edie>Well, this is such a beautiful lawn.
<28-20,Edie>这个草坪真漂亮

660
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:41,200
<28-20,Edie>We could put her to rest right here.
<28-20,Edie>我们让她在这里安睡吧

661
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:43,000
<28-21,Susan>On my front lawn?
<28-21,Susan>在我的前院草坪?

662
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:44,400
<28-22,Edie>Why not?
<28-22,Edie>为什么不?

663
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:49,700
<28-22,Edie>She could spend all of eternity looking at her house and keep an eye on the neighborhood.
<28-22,Edie>她可以永远地注视她的房子 还可以密切关注她的邻居

664
00:40:49,700 --> 00:40:52,100
<28-22,Edie>She'd like that.
<28-22,Edie>她会喜欢那样的

665
00:40:52,100 --> 00:40:55,700
<28-22,Edie>Stand over here. I'll hose you off.
<28-22,Edie>过来站这儿. 我替你冲洗

666
00:40:56,400 --> 00:40:59,100
<28-2,Susan>I don't think so.
<28-2,Susan>我不想这样

667
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:02,300
<28-24,Edie>You owe me.
<28-24,Edie>你欠我的

668
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:13,800
<28-25,Edie>Martha... I'm going to miss you.
<28-25,Edie>Martha... 我会想你的

669
00:41:30,500 --> 00:41:32,900
<29-1,Mary Alice Voiceover>Death is inevitable.
<29-1,Mary Alice Voiceover>(死亡无法避免)

670
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:36,600
<29-1,Mary Alice Voiceover>It's a promise made to each of us at birth.
<29-1,Mary Alice Voiceover>(那是一个我们出生时就许下的诺言)

671
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:44,200
<29-1,Mary Alice Voiceover>But before that promise is kept, we all hope something will happen to us.
<29-1,Mary Alice Voiceover>(但是在诺言兑现之前 我们都希望会有些事情发生)

672
00:41:44,500 --> 00:41:49,400
<29-2,Mary Alice Voiceover>Whether it's the thrill of romance...
<29-2,Mary Alice Voiceover>(不管那是浪漫激情...)

673
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:50,800
<0-0,None>Hey, come back here!
<0-0,None>嗨, 回这儿来!

674
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:52,800
<29-3,Mary Alice Voiceover>The joy of raising a family...
<29-3,Mary Alice Voiceover>(养育孩子的快乐...)

675
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:55,300
<28-4,Susan>I'm going to get you! I'm going to get you!
<28-4,Susan>我来抓你了! 我来抓你了!

676
00:41:55,300 --> 00:42:00,500
<29-4,Mary Alice Voiceover>Or the anguish of great loss...
<29-4,Mary Alice Voiceover>(还是巨大损失的悲痛...)

677
00:42:00,500 --> 00:42:07,300
<29-5,Mary Alice Voiceover>we all hope to experience something that make our lives meaningful.
<29-5,Mary Alice Voiceover>(我们都希望经历一些让生命有意义的事)

678
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:15,200
<29-6,Mary Alice Voiceover>But the sad fact is not all lives have meaning.
<29-6,Mary Alice Voiceover>(但不幸的是并不是所有的生命都有意义)

679
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:22,200
<29-7,Mary Alice Voiceover>Some people spend their time on this planet just sitting on the sidelines...
<29-7,Mary Alice Voiceover>(一些人只是天天坐视旁观...)

